Years to interpolate record to. Charcoal counts, sample volume, and sample depths are all interpolated before calculating charcoal accumulation rates. Enter 0 here is you want to interpolate to the median sample resolution (yr sample-1) of the selected record.
<td>Do you want to transform the record before analysis?  0 == No
column3: 2 == natural log transform. For 1-2, all charcoal accumulation rates have 1 added to them before transformation.

column1: <td>How do you want to estimate low-frequency CHAR (aka Cbackground)? 1 == Lowess smoother
Years to smooth record over for estimating Cbackground.
<td>How do you want to calculate high-frequency CHAR (aka Cpeak)? 1 == residuals (Cpeak = Cinterpolated - Cbackground)
<td>What type of threshold do you want to use? 1 == Globally defined

<td>How do you want to determine the threshold values for peak identification? 1 == user defines threshold values in threshValues (below), 2 == base threshold values on a percentile cut-off of a noise distribution, modeled with a 0- or 1-mean Gaussian (for cPeak method = 1 or 2, respectively)
column2: 3 == same as 2, but noise distribution is determined by a Gaussian mixture model.

column1: What threshold values do you want to evaluate? If threshMethod == 1, these values are in Cpeak units (i.e. either a residual or ratio value). If threshMethod == 2-3, these values are percentiles of the noise distribution (e.g. 0.95). In both cases, the last value (row 20) will be used for peak plotting and peak analysis.
<td>Cut-off probability for minimum count analysis. E.g. if minCountP = 0.05, then the minimum charcoal count within 75 years before a peak has to have &lt
column2: 5% chance of coming from the same Poisson distribution as the maximum charcoal count associated with the peak. Peaks with a probability &gt
column3: 5% will be flagged and displayed but not included in peak analysis. Set this value to 0.99 to turn it off.

column1: Years to smooth fire frequency and fire return intervals over.

<td>Do you want to save the output data by appending it to this file? 0 == no
